3:["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["How Funding Works on ","Hyperliquid"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates BLUR/USDT funding rates every hour based on the premium between perpetual and index prices, with payments occurring automatically between long and short positions. The funding rate formula considers the 1-hour TWAP of the premium, applying a dampening factor to prevent excessive volatility in payments. Positions held at the top of each hour automatically receive or pay funding based on their direction and the prevailing rate. The on-chain nature ensures transparent rate calculations and eliminates counterparty risk in funding settlements."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BLUR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's connection to NFT market cycles creates unique funding rate patterns distinct from traditional DeFi tokens, as sentiment shifts between NFT speculation and utility usage. The token's relatively smaller market cap compared to major cryptocurrencies can lead to more pronounced funding rate premiums during directional moves. Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding intervals provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to the standard 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."}]]}],[["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical BLUR Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR funding rates on Hyperliquid typically exhibit higher volatility during NFT market cycles, with rates often spiking above 0.1% per hour during major collection launches or marketplace updates. The token shows correlation with broader NFT sentiment, creating predictable funding rate patterns around OpenSea competitor announcements and airdrop events. Historical data shows BLUR funding rates can remain persistently negative during bear markets as short interest dominates, while bull phases see rapid positive rate escalation. The 1-hour funding frequency amplifies these patterns, creating more pronounced rate swings compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]]}],["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR/USDT funding rate arbitrage benefits from cross-exchange rate differentials, particularly between Hyperliquid's hourly rates and other platforms' 8-hour cycles. Traders can capitalize on rate convergence by taking opposing positions when Hyperliquid's accumulated hourly rates diverge significantly from competing exchanges. The on-chain nature of Hyperliquid allows for automated arbitrage strategies using smart contracts, reducing execution latency and slippage. Market makers often find opportunities during NFT events when BLUR spot demand creates sustained funding rate premiums that exceed typical trading costs."}]]}],"$L8"],"$L9"]}]
