8:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Mitigation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR funding rate arbitrage carries heightened volatility risk during NFT market stress events, as the underlying asset can experience rapid price movements that exceed funding gains. Hyperliquid's single-chain architecture creates smart contract risk and potential network congestion during high-activity periods. The relatively low liquidity in BLUR compared to major tokens can lead to increased slippage when unwinding large positions, particularly during market stress. Traders should maintain appropriate position sizing and consider the correlation between BLUR price movements and funding rate sustainability when executing strategies."}]]}]
9:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are BLUR/USDT funding rates updated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and paid every hour on Hyperliquid, providing 24 funding payments per day compared to 3 payments on most centralized exchanges. This higher frequency creates more opportunities for funding rate arbitrage but requires active position management."},{"question":"What makes BLUR funding rates different from other tokens on Hyperliquid?","answer":"BLUR funding rates tend to be more volatile due to the token's connection to NFT market cycles and smaller market cap. The rates often show distinct patterns around NFT marketplace events and can sustain higher premiums during speculative periods compared to established DeFi tokens."},{"question":"Can I automate BLUR funding rate arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Yes, Hyperliquid's on-chain architecture supports automated trading strategies through smart contracts and API integration. Many traders use automated systems to monitor funding rates across exchanges and execute arbitrage positions when profitable opportunities arise."},{"question":"What are the typical funding rate ranges for BLUR/USDT on Hyperliquid?","answer":"BLUR funding rates typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per hour during normal market conditions, but can spike above 0.3% during major NFT events or marketplace updates. The wide range reflects the volatile nature of NFT-related tokens and creates significant arbitrage opportunities for active traders."}]}]
